      "content": "right, but if it's just an \"ethical assertion\" then doesn't that mean people use it as a way to shut down any actual debate about the cost or the logistics? like if you call it a right, then anyone who disagrees is basically saying they don't care about human dignity. isn't that kind of a way to bypass the actual economic reality of the situation?",
